#### ___These are list of Upcoming/New/Partially new Data Engineering/Machine Learning Engineering Technologies I prefer to follow in 2021.___ 
       

* [Getdbt](https://www.getdbt.com/) <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRiGblA7uxt_Cdzx89L8v0ar-MP7hHtCQhwhQ&usqp=CAU" width="48" height="22">, Its hitting the sweet spot of Apache Spark, by bringing Simplified SQL based pipeline!
* [Prefect](https://www.prefect.io/) <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="48" height="22">, Designed to make Workflow Management easier & better compared to Apache Airflow 
* [DVC](https://dvc.org/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22">, Open-source Version Control System for Machine Learning Projects & desired for MLOps
* [Great_Expectations](https://greatexpectations.io/) <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQM19MyXBQovpmFSfc53axRTwB75WS1vjEG7g&usqp=CAU" width="28" height="22">, Data Science Testing framework, its already amazing!
* [Amundsen](https://www.amundsen.io/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> An Open Sourced data discovery and metadata engine 
* [Marquez](https://marquezproject.github.io/marquez/) <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="48" height="22"> Open Source Metadata with an amazing UI
* [Dagster](https://dagster.io/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> A data orchestrator for machine learning, very Programming based & in the similar space of Airflow/Prefect but emphasize on State flow
* [Apache Calcite](https://calcite.apache.org/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22">  Framework for building SQL databases and data management systems without owning Data. Hive, flink and other uses Calcite
* [maiot-ZenML](https://zenml.io/) <img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1338858528916717568/3e8Qwq7w_400x400.jpg" width="48" height="22"> Open Sourced MLOps Framework, having bit of everything.
* [Apache Superset](https://superset.apache.org/) <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQMhXJ6LEPBSsQ3wvXYm75xxEJmwtLFFs557w&usqp=CAU" width="48" height="22"> Open Source BI with  many connectors available
* [Metabase](https://www.metabase.com/) <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSImEHTOKyXfhutsDrmGaddH_cPSax9b9WVfA&usqp=CAU" width="48" height="22"> An Open Source BI, with amazing Vizualization
* [Hopswork](https://www.logicalclocks.com/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Open Sourced MLOPs Feature Store
* [Feast](https://feast.dev/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> open-source feature store, now with Tecton
* [MLFlow](https://mlflow.org/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Machine Learning Platform, first of its Kind
* [Pachyderm](https://www.pachyderm.com/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> MLOps Platform, in space of MLFlow
* [Montecarlodata](https://www.montecarlodata.com/) <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="48" height="22"> Data Governance or Data Discovery or Data Observability
* [Tecton](https://www.tecton.ai/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Enterprise Feature Store
* [Fiddler](https://www.fiddler.ai/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Enterprise Explainable AI
* [Cnvrg](https://cnvrg.io/) <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="48" height="22">, Enterprise MLOps
* [RAPIDS](https://rapids.ai/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Data Science on GPU
* [DASK](https://dask.org/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Data Science purely on Python
* [Trino](https://trino.io/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22">, aka PrestoSQL. With clear seperation from Presto, now Trino can focus heavily on features
* [Apache Pinot](https://pinot.apache.org/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Realtime distributed OLAP datastore.Its growth is amazing & Its in the similar space of Druid, but not Exactly!
* [Databricks](https://databricks.com/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22">, with new SQL Analytics and Lakehouse paper, expecting more amazing OSS
* [Delta Lake](https://delta.io/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22">, ACID on Apache Spark
* [Koalas](https://koalas.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Pandas on Apache Spark
* [Apache Beam](https://beam.apache.org/)  <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Simplify Stream Processing, its gaining lots of attention and its slowly moving away from ONLY GCP but more generic
* [Apache Arrow](https://arrow.apache.org/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Extremely important because of non-JVM, in-memory Columnar format & Vectorized
* [Ray](https://ray.io/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Distributed Machine Learning and now Streaming
* [Anodot](https://www.anodot.com/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22">  Monitors all your data in real time for lightning-fast detection of the incidents
* [Data Robot](https://www.datarobot.com/) <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="48" height="22"> Solid ML Platform with strong focus in Enterprise MLOps
* [Dataiku](https://www.dataiku.com/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Enterprise AI/MLOps Platform
* [Fivetran](https://fivetran.com/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Data Integration Pipeline
* [DataFrame Whale](https://docs.whale.cx/) <img src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/fit/t/1600/480/1*ykBy51J1QhJ1BJsPem2KLg.png" width="48" height="22"> Extremely simple data discovery tool
* [Nextflow](https://docs.whale.cx/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Data-driven computational pipelines designed for BioInformatics, but can go beyond
* [Confluent](https://docs.whale.cx/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Apache Kafka & following Ecosystem
* [Papermill](https://papermill.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) <img src="data:image/png;base64," width="48" height="22"> Parameterizing a Notebook, makes Data Science more interesting and easier
* [Nextflow](https://docs.whale.cx/) <img src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/fit/t/1600/480/1*ykBy51J1QhJ1BJsPem2KLg.png" width="48" height="22"> Extremely simple data discovery tool
